You need to make a bigger circle with your right hand when you try to get into the air position; this will help you make more turns. Pass your left leg longer until your right leg and lift your knee during takeoff; it will help you jump higher.
485958767041839121_0.CPM: Instruction: Keep your body more upright and avoid leaning too far forward during the free turn.

CoachMe.best: Try to keep your left hand forward and bring your right foot in closer alignment with your left for a better jump approach.
CoachMe.worst: Try to keep your body straight while in the air to avoid falling forward when you land.

485958767041839121_0.Vila-U: Instruction: When you do free turn, make sure your butt doesn't put out and also your body too much forward.

485956826287046865_0.GT: The way you use your hands when you do takeoff is very weird: You’re not allowed to pre-turn your left shoulder and then use your right shoulder; you should use them together at the same time. Make sure you jump up when you do takeoff. You need to fully straighten yourself in the air position, close your hands tightly, and straighten your body up.
485956826287046865_0.CPM: You should work on maintaining a straight back and not leaning too far forward during your free turn.

CoachMe.best: Try to keep your body muscles firm throughout the jump.
CoachMe.worst: Work on maintaining a straight body line and a downward left leg position in the air.

485956826287046865_0.Vila-U: The learner should extend their left leg forward before doing the landing position.

485956965722489145_0.GT: Here’s a big mistake. You step your right leg too much behind your left leg. It’s very hard to do the takeoff like this. Make sure that your left side doesn’t lift so much because you can destroy your jump, and make sure that your right side is doing a circle around your body when you’re doing the takeoff. Also, use power when you jump up, which is why you don’t have enough height to rotate your jump.
485956965722489145_0.CPM: Instruction: Ensure your body is centered and maintain a straight back during the spin to achieve better balance and control.

CoachMe.best: Practice lengthening the edge that arcs outward forward.
CoachMe.worst: Try to keep your body straight while you are in the air.

485956965722489145_0.Vila-U: The learner should focus on maintaining their balance and not extending their leg forward while doing the landing position.
